rComments: He is a great professor!! He shows about 10 Farside comic strips per class, and he loves his jokes. Overall, the class was pretty easy, just try to go to every class. The discussions are easy points.

If you take this class and don't get an A you should seriously consider dropping out of the university. The class is practically set up to give you a passing grade. I didn't study the entire year and got an A because my discussion grade was so high because of all the extra credit. Take this class, don't buy the textbook. Laugh at the Farside's.

Easy as pie. Good class, interesting stuff... but remember he IS a geology professor; good luck with the rock talks. Never used the textbook, only the class notes and a CD that comes with the book. He's a funny guy, tells great jokes.  I really enjoyed this class.

this class (natural disasters) and prof. are both awesome. not as easy as you may think, but still pretty easy. material is interesting. highlights include him nailing kids with that blue ball and a family throwing rocks at hot lava as it moves towards their house
Professor Altaner is one of the best! I definitely recommend GEO 100 for a gen ed and an easy A, but mostly for Prof. Altaner! Great guy, dry sense of humor. I liked him a lot.

really easy class for physical science gen ed requirement. he starts every class with jokes and then randomly puts jokes up on the projector. personally i think its kind of funny. hes just a weird guy and not everyone appreciates it. he also shows a lot of video clips so the class is not too boring. definitely take this class!
Energetic and fun. His enthusiasm is contagious and keeps your attention. He is helpful and a great guide.

He is very personable and if you like Geology the class would be easy to attend. Attendance is not mandatory for lecture, but is mandatory for the discussion. I had Eric for discussion, and he was very easy to work with! The labs are pretty easy, but the homework is very time consuming. He says there might be pop quizzes, but there weren't!

He is a great teacher. Clarified everything you needed to know for the exam. Did not need to purchase the textbook, we didn't use it. Field trips were fun. It's almost always an enjoyable class when the professor is so interested in the topic. Would recommend environmental geology to anyone

Personally, I thought his incorporation of dry humor and Farside comics were great. I know people who thopught he was boring and not funny whatsoever, but I disagree. I can see how one can find him to be boring though. It just depends, I guess. GEOL-100 is an easy A anyways. Take notes in lecture, no need for the textbook (although it can help).
leads off the class with stand up humor, has intermissions to read some Farside comics each day. his subject isn't very hard and he explains it well. very good teacher.
leads off the class with stand up humor, has intermissions to read some Farside comics each day. his subject isn't very hard and he explains it well. very good teacher.
The discussions are the best part of the class! It gives real hands-on experience with geology!
Getting an A in this class is like taking a dump, i.e., it's relatively painless and will happen naturally. Much like the disasters you'll be studying.

Makes class hysterical!!  Starts off everyday with a fresh Farside cartoon.  Loved the class and him as a professor.  I went to office hours and got to meet his adorable husky too!  A funny dog lover that's passionate about rocks!  Sign me up!

Most likely the easiest class you will ever take in college.  Lectures consist of drawing pictures and watching videos of tornadoes, hurricanes, etc.  Notes are already printed out and just filled in during the lecture.  Studied for about 20 minutes for each test and got a 99% for the class.  Take it!
Very easy, a 20 point homework assignment online every week, 3 pop quizzes over material you did that day so be careful which days you skip.  only one paper, very easy tests!
Don't buy the book. Just study the lecture notes over and over and the tests will be easy. And you don't need to go to lecture either. Great guy

The class can get boring at times but at others its fun. You can miss some lectures so long as you understand whats going on. Go to the reviews for the test, he covers everything that will be on it. And just try on the hmwrk & writing. Easy A. Interesting material. Not a perfect class, but you can do alot worse!
EASY CLASS!
